It was ridiculously difficult to find the subscription option. It was easy last year when I purchased a 6 month membership for the winter, and this year it took me three separate tries to find the bloody option to purchase the membership, mostly because the website is so pushy about trying to bundle other options in, and I had to scroll to the bottom of multiple pages. I enjoy the workout BOD offers, but if I didn't live rurally/going to the gym was more financially feasible, you'd have lost my business with how frustrating it was to finally get there. It shouldn't take a fairly computer literate person that many tries to give you my money. Like I just want to give you my money for some workouts, stop forcing calendars and protein shakes on me. 
Ironically enough, I couldn't even scroll to the bottom of this feedback form to submit it, because the app is so glitchy. At least you provide fun workouts (when the app doesn't glitch and the website works).

I'm struggling with my myx bike. The heat rate monitor pairs and speed my heart rate during workouts, but at the end doesn't track (screen say shows 0's on all heart rate zones and prompt says "next time pair your device...). I've also had trouble with the cadence sensor not always pairing. the battery is full but sometimes it just won't start working, it's very frustrating because if I leave a workout to try to get it to pair I lose the original playlist. and riding without the cadence is annoying.
and lastly, the app doesn't track all my workouts. for example, this morning I did a Barre BODi followed by a cycle 15 and it only takes the ride (said 30 minutes).  these are minor inconveniences, but they are still annoying when you just want to get a quick workout in and things aren't working the way they are supposed to.
